snippet: The father of Lizzy Seeberg, a woman who committed suicide after accusing a Notre Dame football player of sexual assault, says the university was less inclined to thoroughly investigate that case.
abstract: Tom Seeberg, father of Notre Dame student, Lizzy Seeberg, who committed suicide in 2010 after accusing a football player of sexual assault, says university did less to investigate a rape charge than when it found out their star football player had been the victim of a hoax.
lead_paragraph: The father of Lizzy Seeberg, a woman who committed suicide after accusing a Notre Dame football player of sexual assault, says the university was less inclined to thoroughly investigate that case.

headline.seo: Notre Dame Handled Te’o and Seeberg Cases Differently, Some Say
headline.main: In Notre Dame’s Handling of Two Episodes, Some See Inconsistency
headline.print_headline: In Notre Dame’s Handling of Two Episodes, Some See Inconsistency
